Dear Saravanan and Team,

Thank you for the 08 April tracker. The revised format with daily 
progress entries, the PULSE 360 column, Stage 0 sub-status, and Target 
by 11 April columns is good — all seven corrections from my earlier 
review have been applied.

*The developer side of the tracker looks encouraging.* Mariyaiya has the 
PR form FSD in progress with a target of 9 April for PO form Stage 0 
corrections. TL-Dev Sasi has cleaned the RMI contract form dead code, 
generated a draft FSD, and prepared the SPs — all due to the IST team 
today. Annamalai has removed dead code and prepared table, view, and SP 
scripts for four Domestic Sales transactions. Sathiskumar has correctly 
shifted to Daily Attendance transactions as directed and has shared that 
FSD with the IST team. This is solid progress from all four developers.

*However the IST side of this tracker is a serious concern and I need to 
address it directly.
*
*Overdue — Action Items 1, 2, 3, 4*

All four IST members were asked to cross-check their module scope 
against the Excel menu charts and revert to the PM by Monday 6 April 
EoD. Today is Thursday 9 April. All four items are still showing Open 
with no daily progress entry and PULSE 360 = N.

This applies to Muthuvel (M01), PM Saravanan himself (M02), Seenivasan 
(M03), and TL-IST Palanivel (M04). I want to note specifically that PM 
Saravanan's own IST task for M02 is also overdue. The PM asking the team 
to fill PULSE 360 accurately while his own rows show N for three of four 
entries is not acceptable. *Lead by example or the instruction will not 
be followed.
*
*All four scope cross-checks must be completed and submitted to PM 
Saravanan by today, 9 April EoD without fail.*

*Muthuvel — PR Form IST Review*

Action Item 5 — the PR form IST review using the IST-1 to IST-7 
questionnaire — shows no daily progress entry and PULSE 360 = N as of 
today. The Vamshadhara gap document shows progress, which I note. But 
the SPINRISE IST review is the single most critical blocker for the 
first APPROVED FSD milestone. Without Muthuvel's IST sign-off, the PR 
form cannot move to TL-IST, PM, and CEO review. Without those, no 
approved FSD exists. Without an approved FSD, Claude Code cannot begin 
production conversion.

*Muthuvel, I need a clear commitment from you: when will the PR form IST 
review (IST-1 to IST-7) be submitted? Please reply to this mail with a 
specific date.*

*Seenivasan and TL-IST Palanivel
*
Both rows show zero activity, zero PULSE 360 entries, and no daily 
progress across all tasks. The developers you are supporting — Annamalai 
and Sathiskumar — are actively submitting FSD work to the IST team. That 
work is sitting in a queue with no one reviewing it. Please begin your 
IST reviews immediately and update the tracker and PULSE 360 today.

*Abinandan and Hariharan — clarification needed
*
Abinandan is using the PR form corrected critical analysis document as a 
reference for ASP.NET Core development. This is acceptable as a practice 
and trial exercise, consistent with Mariyaiya's clarification earlier 
this week. Please confirm explicitly in your next tracker update that 
this is practice work and not production development against an approved 
FSD.

Hariharan's row shows 'In Progress' in the daily remarks but PULSE 360 = 
N. PM to clarify in the next update: what specifically is Hariharan 
working on, and is it exploratory React familiarisation or production 
development? No approved FSD exists yet for any SPINRISE screen.

*Action Item 6 and Action Item 14*

Action Item 6 (SP identification for all modules) still shows Open even 
though TL-Dev Sasi and Annamalai's daily progress entries confirm SPs 
have been prepared for their modules. PM to update the action item 
status to reflect the actual developer progress.

Action Item 14 (Claude Pro subscriptions for Annamalai and Sathiskumar) 
remains Open. This was due this week. PM Saravanan is the owner. Please 
confirm activation status today.


*Module Summary header*

The Module Summary sheet still shows *'As of 4 April 2026'.* Please 
update to the correct date when submitting the next tracker.


*For Saturday 11 April*

The picture heading into Saturday is this: all four developers are 
active and progressing on Stage 0. The IST side is stalled on scope 
verification and FSD reviews. If this gap is not closed in the next two 
days, developers will arrive at Saturday's meeting with completed Stage 
0 work that has no IST verification against it, and Sprint 0 activation 
will have to be deferred again.

Saravanan, please personally follow up with Muthuvel, Seenivasan, and 
TL-IST Palanivel today and confirm their overdue items are completed by 
EoD 9 April, without deviation.

Regards,
T. Mani

