          three-sheet format — task-level detail, module-level
          visibility, and a numbered action items log — is exactly the
          right approach for a project of this complexity.<br>
          <br>
          <b>However, before I approve this for circulation, please
            address the following.</b><br>
          <br>
          <b>CORRECTIONS AND ADDITIONS REQUIRED</b><br>
          <br>
          <b>1.  Daily update mechanism is missing.</b><br>
          The tracker is titled 'PM Daily Tracker' but currently has no
          column for recording daily progress. As it stands, it captures
          the initial status from the MoM but provides no mechanism to
          update progress day by day between now and Saturday. Please
          add a 'Last Updated' date column and a 'Daily Progress /
          Remarks' column to the PM Daily Tracker sheet. The PM should
          update these every working day. Without daily entries, this
          remains a point-in-time MoM snapshot rather than a living
          tracker.<br>
          <br>
          <b>2.  PULSE 360 reference column is missing.</b><br>
          The MoM stressed PULSE 360 logsheet accuracy as the primary
          daily tracking tool. The tracker should have a 'PULSE 360
          Updated' column (Y / N / Partial) that you verify each day
          against the team's logsheet entries. This column is the bridge
          between the tracker and PULSE 360 — without it, the two
          systems operate independently with no daily cross-check.<br>
